dependencies:
node.js
socket.io

to install

1. move project under htdocs


to run server:

1. install node, socket.io

2. terminal to main directory:

3. ~ node server/server.js


to run client:

load client/game.html in browser

note: 
client runs as localhost - can only access locallly
to run client as an ip (so that other devices can access)

1. update client.game.html:
<script src="http://localhost:8000/socket.io/socket.io.js"></script>
socket = io.connect("http://localhost", {port:8000, transports:["websocket"]});
to use ip/site name

